        result.put("appBenDeductions", "<p><strong>How we&rsquo;ll collect this amount</strong></p> <p>The court has asked Jobcentre Plus to make deductions from your benefits until the full amount is paid.</p> <p>Deductions will be made because you either:</p> <ul> <li>agreed to this</li> <li>failed to pay a penalty in the past</li> <li>have been ordered to pay compensation</li> </ul> <p>If the deduction fails then you must pay the Reserve Terms as stated above.</p> <p><strong>How much will be deducted</strong></p> <p>Your Jobcentre Plus will work out how much to take from your benefits. Contact them and quote your National Insurance number when you get in touch.</p> <p><strong>If we don&rsquo;t receive the deductions from Jobcentre Plus</strong></p> <p>You&rsquo;ll need to pay the balance yourself directly to the court. We&rsquo;ll write to you if this happens and explain what to do.</p> <p><strong>For any questions</strong></p> <p>Contact the Service Centre:</p> <p>Email: <a href=\"mailto:sjs@justice.gov.uk\">sjs@justice.gov.uk</a></p> <p>Telephone: 0300 303 0656 Monday to Friday 9am to 5pm</p>");
        result.put("attachEarnings", "<p><strong>How we&rsquo;ll collect this amount</strong></p> <p>The court has told your employer to make deductions from your pay until the full amount is paid (known as an attachment of earnings order).</p> <p>They decided this because you either:</p> <ul> <li>agreed to this</li> <li>failed to pay a penalty in the past</li> <li>have been ordered to pay compensation</li> </ul> <p>If the deduction fails then you must pay the Reserve Terms as stated above.</p> <p><strong>This is a priority order</strong></p> <p>The amount above must be paid before any non-priority orders you may have (even if they were made before this order).</p> <h2>Check your employer details</h2> <p><strong>Employer</strong></p> <p><strong>As stated above</strong></p> <p>You must contact us within 7 days if:</p> <ul> <li>your employer details are wrong</li> <li>you leave your employer for a new one - you&rsquo;ll need to include the name of your new employer, job title, gross pay, National Insurance number, payroll or employee number</li> </ul> <p><em>You may be fined if you don&rsquo;t let the court know the correct details.</em></p> <h2>How much will be taken from your pay?</h2> <p>This depends on your earnings after tax and pensions have been taken off.</p> <table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; height: 136px;\" border=\"1\"> <tbody> <tr style=\"height: 17px;\"> <td style=\"width: 25%; height: 17px;\">Daily earnings</td> <td style=\"width: 25%; height: 17px;\">Weekly earnings</td> <td style=\"width: 25%; height: 17px;\">Monthly earnings</td> <td style=\"width: 25%; height: 17px;\">% to be deducted each time you're paid</td> </tr> <tr style=\"height: 17px;\"> <td style=\"width: 25%; height: 17px;\">&pound;0.00 - &pound;8.00</td> <td style=\"width: 25%; height: 17px;\">&pound;0.00 - &pound;55.00</td> <td style=\"width: 25%; height: 17px;\">&pound;0.00 - &pound;220.00</td> <td style=\"width: 25%; height: 17px;\">0%</td> </tr> <tr style=\"height: 17px;\"> <td style=\"width: 25%; height: 17px;\">&pound;8.01 - &pound;15.00</td> <td style=\"width: 25%; height: 17px;\">&pound;55.01 - &pound;100.00</td> <td style=\"width: 25%; height: 17px;\">&pound;220.01 - &pound;400.00</td> <td style=\"width: 25%; height: 17px;\">3%</td> </tr> <tr style=\"height: 17px;\"> <td style=\"width: 25%; height: 17px;\">&pound;15.01 - &pound;20.00</td> <td style=\"width: 25%; height: 17px;\">&pound;100.01 - &pound;135.00</td> <td style=\"width: 25%; height: 17px;\">&pound;400.01 - &pound;540.00</td> <td style=\"width: 25%; height: 17px;\">5%</td> </tr> <tr style=\"height: 17px;\"> <td style=\"width: 25%; height: 17px;\">&pound;20.01 - &pound;24.00</td> <td style=\"width: 25%; height: 17px;\">&pound;135.01 - &pound;165.00</td> <td style=\"width: 25%; height: 17px;\">&pound;540.01 - &pound;660.00</td> <td style=\"width: 25%; height: 17px;\">7%</td> </tr> <tr style=\"height: 17px;\"> <td style=\"width: 25%; height: 17px;\">&pound;24.01 - &pound;38.00</td> <td style=\"width: 25%; height: 17px;\">&pound;165.01 - &pound;260.00</td> <td style=\"width: 25%; height: 17px;\">&pound;660.01 - &pound;1040.00</td> <td style=\"width: 25%; height: 17px;\">12%</td> </tr> <tr style=\"height: 17px;\"> <td style=\"width: 25%; height: 17px;\">&pound;38.01 - &pound;53.00</td> <td style=\"width: 25%; height: 17px;\">&pound;260.01 - &pound;370.00</td> <td style=\"width: 25%; height: 17px;\">&pound;1040.01 - &pound;1480.00</td> <td style=\"width: 25%; height: 17px;\">17%</td> </tr> <tr style=\"height: 17px;\"> <td style=\"width: 25%; height: 17px;\">&pound;53.01 or more</td> <td style=\"width: 25%; height: 17px;\">&pound;370.01 or more</td> <td style=\"width: 25%; height: 17px;\">&pound;1480.01 or more</td> <td style=\"width: 25%; height: 17px;\">17% of lowest amount here and 50% of anything over</td> </tr> </tbody> </table> <p>Your employer will keep making deductions in each payroll, until the full amount you owe is paid.</p> <p>(If we don&rsquo;t receive the full amount in deductions, you&rsquo;ll need to pay the balance directly to the court. We&rsquo;ll write to you if this happens and explain what to do.)</p> <h2>Help and advice</h2> <p><strong>For any questions</strong></p> <p>Contact the Service Centre:</p> <p>Email: <a href=\"mailto:sjs@justice.gov.uk\">sjs@justice.gov.uk</a></p> <p>Telephone: 0300 303 0656 Monday to Friday 9am to 5pm</p>");
